PLOT

"The Clash of the Titans" is set in the Greek city of Argos where a war 
is about to explode between man and the gods. Perseus (Sam Worthington)
raised as a fisherman, but is actually a demi-god. Perseus is the son of 
Zeus (Liam Neeson) who is about to take on the gods after the death of his 
family. Zeus' brother Hades (Ralph Fiennes) was the one who killed his 
family, and Perseus wants to kill him. However, it is Perseus's destiny 
to rescue the city of Argos from the ruthless rage of Hades and his Kraken 
monster. With nothing to lose, Perseus leads a band of soldiers on a quest 
to defeat the Kraken. In doing this, Perseus will prevent Hades from
